// here we are gonna learn vector in c++ ;

// vector is a data structure to store data , its same as array the only diff is it is dynamic like we dont neeed to specify the size of vectore when we intialize vctor:-

// 1) vector<int>v;
// 2) vector<int>v={1,2,3,4};
// 3) vector<int>v(5,0); so it means this is vector of size 5 and all values are zero ;
// 4) Funciton :-

// 1) size =vector.size();
// 2) push_back()=v.push_back(2);
// 3) pop_back()=v.pop_back();
// 4) v.front()=print first value
// 5) v.back()= print last value
// 6) v.at(0) is same as v[0]

// Static vs dynamic :-

// static -> compile time -> int a[5]; array  _> memory stored in stack
// dynamic -> runtime -> vector -> memory stored in heap 


// how to make pair in vector sometime we need to store indices and values:-
// vector<pair<int,int>>x;
// x.push_back({2,3});
// access:-
// x[0].first  & x[0].second


